Applications and Use Cases

    Lead Optimization: Improve existing compounds for better binding and properties
    Fragment-to-Lead: Expand fragment hits into drug-like molecules
    Scaffold Hopping: Find alternative scaffolds for known active compounds
    Novel Target Exploration: Design compounds for newly characterized binding sites
    PROTAC Design: Create proteolysis-targeting chimeras with optimized linkers
    Drug Repurposing: Identify new applications for existing molecular frameworks

Future Enhancements

    Deep Learning Integration: Transformer-based molecular generation models
    Protein Flexibility: Dynamic binding site conformational sampling
    ADMET Prediction: Integrated pharmacokinetic property prediction
    Cloud Deployment: Scalable cloud-based infrastructure
    Collaborative Features: Multi-user project management and sharing

LigandForge 2.0 represents a significant advancement in computational drug design by integrating cutting-edge AI techniques with rigorous structure-based design principles, providing researchers with a powerful, accessible tool for modern drug discovery.







